<div class="row g-4">
  <div class="col-lg-7 d-flex flex-column gap-4">
    <section class="card shadow-sm border-0">
      <div class="card-body">
        <p class="text-uppercase text-muted small fw-semibold mb-1">HTML Enhancement Toolkit</p>
        <h1 class="h3 mb-3">Small, declarative sprinkles on server-rendered HTML</h1>
        <p class="mb-0">
          This sample page renders a couple of components from <code>test-app/components</code> and wires in their
          client-side behavior via <code>het</code>. Inspect the markup to see the <code>het-*</code> attributes that
          connect the DOM to the component logic defined in the bundled config.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="card shadow-sm border-0">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="h5 mb-3">Tabs component</h2>
        <p class="text-muted">
          The tabs below are rendered on the server using data passed to the template. Focus them and use the arrow keys
          to cycle between panels; the component handles accessibility state and transitions.
        </p>
        {{> components/tabs tabs=tabs }}
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="col-lg-5">
    <section class="card shadow-sm border-0">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="h5 mb-3">Counter component</h2>
        <p class="text-muted">
          Buttons invoke methods registered in the component setup, updating a signal-backed counter without a page
          refresh.
        </p>
        {{> components/counter }}
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</div>
